' bug-373: a user RESOURCE may not reuse a built-in resource type's name.
' `File` and `Socket` are both BUILTIN_RESOURCES keys, so each declaration is
' rejected with RESOURCE_SHADOWS_BUILTIN at check time.
'
' Before the fix these did not collide-check at all: the built-in's close op
' still pulled its runtime helper into the module while the user's CLOSE BY was
' what actually ran, and the build died downstream in the NIR validator with the
' internal, span-less `NIR declares unused runtime helper 'fs'`. This fixture
' pins that the collision is refused here, with a rule code and a span on the
' RESOURCE line, and never reaches that invariant.
'
' The non-colliding contrast is `native-resource-link-valid`, which declares the
' same shape of native resource under the names `Db`/`Stmt` and still compiles.
RESOURCE File CLOSE BY demoLink::close
RESOURCE Socket CLOSE BY demoLink::finalize

LINK "sqlite3" AS demoLink
  FUNC open(path AS String) AS RES File
    SYMBOL "sqlite3_open"
    ABI (path CString, db OUT CPtr) AS status CInt32
    RETURN db
    SUCCESS_ON status = 0
  END FUNC

  FUNC close(RES db AS File) AS Nothing
    SYMBOL "sqlite3_close"
    ABI (db CPtr) AS status CInt32
    SUCCESS_ON status = 0
  END FUNC

  FUNC finalize(RES sock AS Socket) AS Nothing
    SYMBOL "sqlite3_finalize"
    ABI (sock CPtr) AS status CInt32
    SUCCESS_ON status = 0
  END FUNC
END LINK
